These instructions provide a step-by-step guide for installing cc65 on the distributions that are supported by the [https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/EPEL/FAQ Fedora EPEL repository].

== Step 1: Enable the Fedora EPEL repository ==

To enable Fedora EPEL for your distribution, please refer to the [https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/EPEL Quickstart Guide for Fedora EPEL].

After enabling Fedora EPEL, it is recommended to update the repository cache of the package manager.

<pre>
sudo yum makecache
</pre>

== Step 2: Install cc65 ==

To install the cc65 compiler (and additional things) you can proceed using the [https://github.com/cc65/wiki/wiki/Fedora-Linux instructions for Fedora Linux].

You may need to replace <pre>dnf</pre> command with <pre>yum</pre> eventually.